      "## Matching the diffuser to your space",
      "### One room up to 1,500 sq ft: Autivara Home Room",
      "This is the most common pick. The [Autivara Home Room](/product/autivora-volcano-flame-diffuser) ($109) is a **standalone** unit that covers up to 1,500 sq ft — enough for a living room, a primary suite, a studio apartment, a retail boutique, or a small office. No installation, no HVAC access needed: set it down, load your oil, and it fills the space.",
      "[[cta]]Shop Autivara Home Room — $109|/product/autivora-volcano-flame-diffuser",
      "### A whole house up to 5,000 sq ft: Autivara Home",
      "When you want *every room* scented evenly from a single device, you need HVAC integration. The [Autivara Home](/product/autivora-wood-grain-diffuser) ($199) connects to your central air handler and distributes fragrance through your existing ductwork, covering up to 5,000 sq ft. This is the right call for multi-bedroom houses, two-story layouts, and open floor plans where a single standalone unit would leave cold spots.",
      "[[cta]]Shop Autivara Home — $199|/product/autivora-wood-grain-diffuser",
      "## How to choose if you're between sizes",
      "Three quick rules resolve almost every borderline case. First, **measure volume, not just area** — if your ceilings are over 8 feet or the space opens to a stairwell, size up. Second, **count the doorways** — if scent needs to travel between connected rooms, you're scenting one combined volume, so lean toward HVAC with the [Autivara Home](/product/autivora-wood-grain-diffuser). Third, **think about where it'll grow** — if you're scenting one room now but expect to want the whole house later, the $199 Home saves you from buying twice. Once your hardware is matched to the space, browse the full [Fragrance Oils](/scents) range (from $19) to dial in intensity and mood.",
      "## The bottom line",
